<h3 class="govuk-heading-s">Limited company</h3>

<p class="govuk-body"> To match a limited company, ask the user for:</p>

<ul class="govuk-list govuk-list--bullet">
  <li>the business type</li>
<li> the company registration number </li>
  <li><a class="govuk-link" href="../unique-taxpayer-reference/">Unique taxpayer reference </a>for the business</li>
  <li>postcode for the business</li>
</ul>
<p class="govuk-body"> If the details are correct, allow the user confirm the business name to complete business matching and continue to the service.</p>
<p class="govuk-body"> If the details do not match, provide guidance on  </p>



<h3 class="govuk-heading-s">To match a sole trader</h3>

<p class="govuk-body"> Ask the user for:</p>

<ul class="govuk-list govuk-list--bullet">
  <li>the business type</li>
  <li>the self assessment unique taxpayer reference</li>
  <li> the postcode for the business</li>
</ul>
<p class="govuk-body"> If the details match, then business matching is complete allowing the user continue to the service. However, where the name is not a match, business matching cannot be done. </p>


<h3 class="govuk-heading-s">To match a partnership</h3>

<p class="govuk-body"> Ask the user for:</p>
<ul class="govuk-list govuk-list--bullet">
  <li>the business type</li>
  <li>unique tax reference for the business</li>
  <li> the postcode for the business</li>
  <li> the company registration number (for limited partnerships)</li>
</ul>
<p class="govuk-body"> If the details match, then business matching is complete allowing the user continue to the service. However, where the name is not a match, business matching cannot be done. </p>



